  "text": "As an effective method for analyzing large and complex stochastic models, mean field theory is widely used in many areas. Using mean field theory, the effect of all other individuals on any given individual is approximated by a single averaged effect. Like the work of Sabbadin et al. [CITATION_1] , we applied mean field approximation which approximates a multidimensional distribution ( 1 , 2 , . . . , ) as the joint distribution of independent variables 1 , . . . , . should be as close to as possible according to Kullback-Leibler divergence:",
